# Dr Olatunji Johnson

Lecturer in Statistics in the Department of Mathematics at [**The University of Manchester**](https://www.manchester.ac.uk/)\
Former post-doctoral researcher and PhD student at **CHICAS**, Lancaster Medical School, **Lancaster University** (UK).\
PhD supervisors: **Prof. Peter Diggle**, **Prof. Emanuele Giorgi**, **Prof. Jo Knight**.

My research develops novel geospatial statistical methodology for analyzing epidemiological data, with current work on Neglected Tropical Diseases (NTDs) in low-resource settings. Iâ€™m also the author of the SDALGCP R package.

